            <p>Your facebook is a public information and that is the reason your facebook information such as name and picture can be part of our network without your knowledge. </p>

            <p>But if you do not want your facebook information to be part of our network we will be sad, but that is ok. You can go to settings and chose the option REMOVE MY PROFILE. But we love you and anytime you want to come back, just log into Goleak again and you will be very welcome. </p>

            <p>If we are forced to  by the law, we can show the identity of who wrote the leak, so be nice when you decide to leak someone.</p>







        </div>

        <!-- Example row of columns -->
        


    </div>
    <div class="panel-footer" style="text-align:center">
        <a href="@Url.Content("~/Home/About")">About Us</a> -  <a href="@Url.Content("~/Home/Contact")">Contact</a> - <a href="@Url.Content("~/Tour/Step-1.htm")">Tour</a>
    </div>
</body>
</html>

